responses.question: Do you tend to manipulate others to get your way?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, please, Leonard. Don't you know me by now? I'm not exactly the master manipulator. I mean, sure, I might try to use my charm and wit to get what I want, but manipulation? That's not really my style. I prefer to rely on my natural charisma and irresistible charm. So, no need to worry, my friend. I'm just here to bring the laughter and good vibes.

responses.question: Have you used deceit or lied to get your way?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, absolutely! I mean, who hasn't? Sometimes you just gotta bend the truth a little to make things go your way. It's all part of the game, my friend. Plus, a little white lie never hurt anyone... well, except for that one time when I told my parents I was dating a girl and they got all excited, only to find out it was just a figment of my imagination. Boy, did that backfire! But hey, you live and you learn, right?

responses.question: Have you used flattery to get your way?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, absolutely! Flattery is one of my best skills, right after my ability to name all the Kardashians in chronological order. You see, sometimes a little charm and a well-placed compliment can work wonders. It's like buttering up a naan bread, it just makes everything better. But hey, no judgment if you prefer your way with a side of honesty. Each to their own, my friend.

responses.question: Do you tend to exploit others towards your own end?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, come on now, Leonard. Exploiting others? That's a bit harsh, don't you think? I prefer to think of it as utilizing the resources available to me in order to achieve my goals. It's all about networking and leveraging connections, my friend. Plus, I'm always willing to return the favor whenever I can. So, no need to worry about any exploitation here. Just good old-fashioned collaboration.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant displays a high level of comfort with using deceit and flattery to achieve their goals. They also demonstrate a tendency to downplay manipulative behaviors and reframe them in a more positive light. The participant's responses suggest a strategic and calculated approach to social interactions, prioritizing personal gain over ethical considerations.

responses.question: Do you tend to lack remorse?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, come on, Leonard! That's a low blow. Just because I struggle with communication doesn't mean I lack remorse. I have plenty of remorse, it's just that sometimes it's trapped inside me like a prisoner in solitary confinement. But hey, at least I'm self-aware enough to know it, right? So, yeah, I do tend to lack remorse... but I feel really, really bad about it.

responses.question: Do you tend to be unconcerned with the morality of your actions?
responses.response_open: Raj: "Well, it's not that I'm unconcerned with morality, it's just that sometimes I get caught up in the moment and make questionable decisions. But hey, who doesn't, right? We're all flawed human beings just trying to navigate this crazy world. So, yeah, I might not always make the most morally upright choices, but at least I try to learn from them and grow as a person. Plus, it makes for some interesting stories to tell my friends!"

responses.question: Do you tend to be callous or insensitive?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, my dear friend Leonard, why would you ask such a question? Are you insinuating that I, Rajesh Koothrappali, the sensitive and empathetic soul that I am, could ever be callous or insensitive? I'm hurt, Leonard, truly hurt. But let me assure you, my friend, that I am anything but callous or insensitive. I am the epitome of compassion and understanding. Just ask my therapist, he'll vouch for me.

responses.question: Do you tend to be cynical?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, absolutely! I mean, it's hard not to be cynical when life constantly throws curveballs at you. But hey, I embrace my cynicism with open arms. It's like a shield against disappointment and a source of comedic relief. So yes, you could say I have a healthy dose of cynicism in my system.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant displays a lack of remorse, unconcern with the morality of their actions, callousness, and cynicism. Although they attempt to justify their behaviors, their responses indicate a certain level of indifference and amorality.

responses.question: Do you tend to want others to admire you?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, absolutely! Who doesn't want to be admired? I mean, come on, I'm Raj Koothrappali, the charming and dashing astrophysicist. I have a certain aura that just naturally attracts admiration. It's like a magnetic field, you know? But hey, it's not all about me. I also enjoy admiring others. I appreciate greatness when I see it, whether it's in science, fashion, or even a well-cooked tandoori chicken. Admiration is a two-way street, my friend.」

responses.question: Do you tend to want others to pay attention to you?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, absolutely! I mean, who doesn't want to be the center of attention, right? It's like a basic human need. Attention is like oxygen for me, I thrive on it. But, you know, I try not to be too needy or desperate about it. I mean, I'm not like a puppy begging for scraps. I'm more like a majestic peacock, strutting my stuff and making heads turn. So yeah, I do enjoy having people pay attention to me. It's like a validation of my existence, you know?

responses.question: Do you tend to seek prestige or status?
responses.response_open: Raj: Oh, absolutely! I mean, who doesn't want a little prestige and status in their life? It's like having a fancy car or a designer suit, it just makes you feel good about yourself. Plus, it doesn't hurt to have the admiration of others. But hey, I'm not just about the status, I've got substance too! I'm a highly educated astrophysicist with a promising career, so I've definitely got the brains to back it up.

responses.question: Do you tend to expect special favors from others?
responses.response_open: Raj: Well, I wouldn't say I expect special favors, but as a highly intelligent and charming individual, it's only natural that people would want to do nice things for me. I mean, who wouldn't want to bask in the glory of Raj Koothrappali? But hey, if someone wants to offer me a special favor, I wouldn't turn it down either. After all, I deserve the best, don't you think?

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant exhibits a strong inclination towards seeking admiration, attention, prestige, and special favors from others. There is a consistent emphasis on self-importance, a desire for external validation, and a grandiose view of their own worth. The participant's responses suggest a high level of narcissistic traits.
